>mongo commands (errors you may get check those accordingly)
Basic level issues you may face for linux users (check the below errors if you face any kind of issues follow the following steps):
- follow the mongodb official website commands for installation.
Any kind of basic level issues follow these(max you can solve those by following below 4 commands):
1. sudo service mongod stop 
2. mongod --repair
3. sudo service mongod star
4. mongod --dbpath /usr/local/data/db
- sudo apt-get remove mongodb* --purge (complete removal of mongo from your system).
- sudo rm /tmp/mongodb-27017.sock(***aborting after fassert() failure).
- mongod --dbpath /usr/local/data/db (Failed to stop mongod.service: Unit mongod.service not loaded).
- mongo official website dont follow it for specific version download(http://www.techoism.com/install-mongodb-3-4-ubuntu-16-0414-04/).
- leave this command when your trying through official website (sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org) because based on already existing key it will consider updated version and.
following issues will be faced when you shutdown or restart your system:
- when your system got shutdown/when you restart you system(If you find these errors follow 3 steps in order (i.e 1.sudo service mongod stop, 2.mongod --repair 3.mongod --dbpath /usr/local/data/db)).
- sudo kill all mongod ( when your system got shutdown/when you restart you system, sudo service mongod restart, mongod --dbpath /usr/local/data/db ).
- listen(): bind() failed Address already in use for socket: 0.0.0.0:27017(1.mongod --repair 2.sudo service mongod start 3.mongod --dbpath /usr/local/data/db  )
